node.title: NSW records 30 deaths from COVID-19, slight increase in hospitalisations
node.alt: people lining up outside 4cyte pathology testing site
node.description: NSW records a slight increase in hospitalisations, to 2,762 patients, and 30 new COVID-19 deaths in the 24 hours to 8pm yesterday.
node.content: ["There were 30 COVID-19 deaths reported in the 24 hours to 8pm yesterday in NSW.", "The number of people with the virus in the state\u2019s hospitals increased to 2,762, while ICU admissions were down slightly, to 204.", "A total of 20,148 new cases were reported (8,566 RATs, 11,582 \u00a0PCR).", "More to come."]
